RACE.RACE_TEXT: FAIR GROUNDS RACE 1 1M Dirt CR: 60. Claiming Purse 15000. FOR ACCREDITED LA BRED FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Weight, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since December 1 Allowed 3 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ANYOTHERQUESTIONS took a brush from an inner rival at the start, was void of early speed, trailed two wide into the far turn, picked up stride turning for home before fanning to the six path entering the lane, then sustained a rally outside of foes to reel in the leader at the wire. DEMON HUNTER laid off of the pace in the three path, gained in the four path around the far turn, rallied to reach the front inside the final sixteenth, but was caught at the wire by an outer oncharging rival. JUJU NINETEEN came out at the start, tracked two wide, bid for the lead entering the lane, led at the furlong grounds, but was outkicked inside the final sixteenth, and yielded. BLUE RIDGE RED broke in, rushed clear nearing the first turn, showed the way around the far turn, but was headed in upper stretch, and weakened in the final furlong. SNEAKY ALLIE KAT was slow leaving the gates, trailed, and made little impact. MAGNOLIA RIDGE stalked along the inside, but came under a stiff drive entering the far turn, failed to respond, and weakened through the lane. K T'S JILTED GROOM raced in midpack three wide into the first turn, tucked behind foes nearing the backstretch, then gave way. THE SEVEN FURLONG FRACTION WAS ORIGINALLY HAND-TIMED BUT CHANGED FOLLOWING REVIEW, THE UPDATED FINAL TIME WAS COLLECTED ELECTRONICALLY.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: PLEMMONSTON tracked two wide, then along the inside around the far turn, split the leaders three wide at the furlong grounds, and drove clear. MAX PANDOWDY trailed, improved in the three to four path around the far turn before swinging five wide in upper stretch, stayed on to bid along with inner foes in midstretch, but failed to match strides with the eventual winner in the final furlong while pulling clear of the rest. OKUDAH set the pace in the three to two path around the first turn, met DA GOLD ROOM's rail challenge at the five furlong pole, sparred with that one around the far turn and through upper stretch, but was outkicked by outer rivals at the furlong grounds, and yielded between horses. DA GOLD ROOM tracked along the inside, produced an early bid for the lead inside of the pace setter with five furlongs to go, dueled around the far turn and into upper stretch, but was outkicked by outer bidders at the furlong grounds, and gave way. LUCKY CRUSADER rushed outside of foes to stalk the leader from the five to four path around the first turn, but gave way down the backstretch, and was done early.

OURS AND THEIRS laid off of the pace two wide, got floated three to four wide around the turn, shifted out to the seven path in midstretch, and improved late. SIENNA BREEZE stalked three wide, inched closer to striking range at the five sixteenths pole, but drifted six wide entering the lane, and yielded on her left lead. GATOR PROUD laid off of the pace along the inside, shifted out and between horses turning for home, came into the lane five wide, but lacked a kick to split rivals thereafter. HALF KOO KOO pressed outside of the leader, but failed to keep pace in the four path at the quarter pole, weakened between horses in midstretch, and shied mildly from an inner rival at the sixteenth pole. AKIANE'S SOLDIER laid off of the pace three to four wide, got floated five wide at the five sixteenths pole before fanning seven wide entering the lane, and was outrun.
